attribute.description:
If allowglissandi is off, since a note might correspond to a segment of frames, this attribute determines the way in which pitches and velocities are given to any note:
- First: The notes keeps the pitch and velocity of its first frame;
- Mean (default): The partial takes the mean pitch and velocity;
- Median: The partial takes as pitch/velocity the median of the pitches/velocities of each frame.
If allowglissandi is on, this attribute does not affect anything.
